
[1]drop

   DROP, n. [G.]

   1. A small portion of any fluid in a spherical form, which falls at
   once from any body, or a globule of any fluid which is pendent, as if
   about to fall; a small portion of water falling in rain; as a drop of
   water; a drop of blood; a drop of laudanum.

   2. A diamond hanging from the ear; an earring; something hanging in the
   form of a drop.

   3. A very small quantity of liquor; as, he had not drank a drop.

   4. The part of a gallows which sustains the criminal before he is
   executed, and which is suddenly dropped.
